6:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Galileo AI and Khroma share a solid foundation of core features including Ai Generation, Export Formats. Where Galileo AI pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Responsive, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on this capability. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Galileo AI holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Khroma scores 6/10 overall and 8/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Khroma comes in at a lower starting price of Free, while Galileo AI begins at $19/mo. Khroma stands out by offering a free plan, giving you a risk-free way to explore the platform. Galileo AI requires a paid subscription from the start."}]]}]
